defaultQ312default              defaultChair:default How many layers are between you and the force crime registrar?
default              defaultSir Bernard Hogan-Howedefault: In the Met, you are probably talking about three.  In another force, you could be talking about one.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ1 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default So if the force crime registrar has a problem, they have to go through three layers of management to get to you?
default              defaultSir Bernard Hogan-Howedefault: That is what I was about to explain.  The registrar has access to a commander.  In the Met, we have a Commissioner, a deputy and a board consisting of Assistant Commissioners.  We have another team, which no other force has, called “Deputy Assistant Commissioners” because of the size of the organisation, and then we have Commanders.  So the Commander, who is a chief officer at director level, meets with the crime registrar every four weeks.  They have a meeting
default, which I think is called the SCIRG
default meeting.  What it means is that they look at the integrity of our crime data—so a regular, frequent check.  The crime registrar also meets the Assistant Commissioner for Territorial Policing every 12 weeks, and they produce reports that are then audited
default—
defaultand can be audited
default—
defaultby our Deputy Mayor.  In fact, that is one of the things that we share with them, too.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ313default              defaultChair:default You are statutorily responsible for the crime statistics in the force.  How often do you meet the force crime registrar?
default              defaultSir Bernard Hogan-Howedefault: In the past, we have not met, but as a result of your Committee’s inquiries I will be meeting them in future twice a year.  Now, you might say “Why is it that you have only just started doing this?”  The fact is that the Met is a very big beast, with 50,000 people.  It is a very big city, and of all of the priorities, it has not been the major one.  Broadly, as I have said earlier, I was reassured that we have good systems.  But this officer has raised issues, so I think I have to ensure that I am happy, not only that the systems are happy, and therefore I will be seeing him twice a year.
default&#xa0;
